df_indiv_params <- tibble(
  media = factor(1:3),
  alpha = c(.6, .8, .8),
  theta = c(5, 3, 4),
  kappa = rep(.2, 3),
  s = 1:3,
  beta = c(.8, .6, .3)
) %>% mutate(
  L = rep(13, n()),
  tau = rep(10, n()),
  gamma = rep(-.5, n()),
  err_sigma = rep(.05, n())
) %>% group_by(media) %>% nest %>% rename(param = data) %>% ungroup
# 
set.seed(42)

df_sim <- tibble(
  week = seq(ymd("2020-01-01"), ymd("2021-01-01"), "1 week")
)
#  tidy 
df <- df_indiv_params %>%
  mutate(data = map(
    param,
    function(para, id){
      mutate(df_sim,
             spend = rnorm(n())^2,
             spend_ast = slide_dbl(
               spend,
               function(s) {
                 para <- as.list(para)
                 adstock(s, geo_weight, L = para$L, args = para[c("alpha", "theta")])
                 },
               .before = para$L, .complete = F
               )
             )
      }
    )
    ) %>% dplyr::select(-param) %>% unnest(data)
 

df_out <- left_join(
  df,
  df_indiv_params %>% unnest(param) %>% dplyr::select(media, kappa, s, beta),
  by = "media") %>%
  group_by(week) %>% summarise(sales = sum(beta * hill(spend_ast, kappa, s))) %>%
  mutate(price = arima.sim(list(order = c(1, 1, 1), ar = .3, ma = .4), n = n())[-1],
         sales = sales + df_indiv_params$param[[1]]$tau + rnorm(n(), df_indiv_params$param[[1]]$err_sigma)
         ) %>%
  right_join(pivot_wider(df, week, media, values_from = spend, names_prefix = "media-"), by = "week")

require(microbenchmark)
model_origin <-
  stan_model(
    file = file.path("models", "original-fixed.stan"),
    model_name = "original",
    verbose = T
  )

set.seed(42)
bench <- list()
for(i in seq(3, 20, by = 5)){
  bench[[as.character(i)]] <- microbenchmark(
    sampling(
      model_origin,
      data = d,
      chains = 1
    ),
    times = 20,
    setup = {
      df_indiv_params <- tibble(
        media = factor(1:i),
        alpha = runif(i, 0, 1),
        theta = runif(i, 1, 10),
        kappa = rep(.2, i),
        s = 1:i,
        beta = runif(i, 0, 1)
      ) %>% mutate(
        L = rep(13, n()),
        tau = rep(10, n()),
        gamma = rep(-.5, n()),
        err_sigma = rep(.05, n())
      ) %>% group_by(media) %>% nest %>% rename(param = data) %>% ungroup
      df_sim <- tibble(
        week = seq(ymd("2020-01-01"), ymd("2021-01-01"), "1 week")
      )
      df <- df_indiv_params %>%
        mutate(data = map(
          param,
          function(para, id){
            mutate(df_sim,
                   spend = rnorm(n())^2,
                   spend_ast = slide_dbl(
                     spend,
                     function(s) {
                       para <- as.list(para)
                       adstock(s, geo_weight, L = para$L, args = para[c("alpha", "theta")])
                     },
                     .before = para$L, .complete = F
                   )
            )
          }
        )
        ) %>% dplyr::select(-param) %>% unnest(data)
      df_out <- left_join(
        df,
        df_indiv_params %>% unnest(param) %>% dplyr::select(media, kappa, s, beta),
        by = "media") %>%
        group_by(week) %>% summarise(sales = sum(beta * hill(spend_ast, kappa, s))) %>%
        mutate(price = arima.sim(list(order = c(1, 1, 1), ar = .3, ma = .4), n = n())[-1],
               sales = sales + df_indiv_params$param[[1]]$tau + rnorm(n(), df_indiv_params$param[[1]]$err_sigma)
        ) %>%
        right_join(pivot_wider(df, week, media, values_from = spend, names_prefix = "media-"), by = "week")
      d <- to_stan_data(df_out, L = 13)
    }
  )
}
write_rds(bench, "tmp-benchmark.rds")
